<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="concept_pmc_jk1_1x">
 <title>Custom Stage Libraries</title>
 <conbody>
  <p><indexterm>custom stages<indexterm>libraries</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>user
                    libraries<indexterm>storing</indexterm></indexterm>If you develop custom stages,
            store the stage libraries in a local directory external to the <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
            installation directory. Use an external directory to enable use of the custom stage
            libraries after <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
            upgrades.</p>
        <p>Use the required procedure for your installation type.</p>
        <p>We have tutorials for creating a custom origin, processor, and destination on our
            StreamSets tutorials page. To check them out, go to: <xref
                href="https://github.com/streamsets/tutorials" format="html" scope="external"/>. </p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
